Comment (src/views/admin/NotificationsView.vue:1484):
`ensureActiveTabDataLoaded()` can trigger multiple concurrent `loadHealth()` calls: when the Health tab is selected, `hasLoadedHealth` stays false until the first request finishes, so switching away/back while `healthLoading` is still true will start another request. The older response can then overwrite newer state, and it creates unnecessary traffic. Consider adding a request-sequence/abort guard to `loadHealth()` (similar to `loadJobs()`), or at least short-circuit in `ensureActiveTabDataLoaded()` when `healthLoading` is already true so tab toggles can’t enqueue duplicate loads.

Implementation guidance: In src/views/admin/NotificationsView.vue, prevent duplicate/stale Health tab loads. Add a health request sequence variable near the other request sequence state, e.g. let healthRequestSequence = 0. In loadHealth(), capture const requestSequence = ++healthRequestSequence before setting healthLoading/healthError. After axios.get resolves, only assign health.value if requestSequence still equals healthRequestSequence. In catch, only assign health.value = null and healthError.value if the request is still current. In finally, only set hasLoadedHealth.value = true and healthLoading.value = false if the request is still current, so an older request cannot overwrite newer state or clear loading. Also add a cheap guard in ensureActiveTabDataLoaded(tab) so the Health branch calls loadHealth() only when !hasLoadedHealth.value && !healthLoading.value. Preserve existing UX of clearing healthError at the start of the newest request.
